text: Devil's Lake State Park in Baraboo, Wisconsin, is a popular natural destination centered around a 360-acre lake with sandy beaches and nearly 30 miles of hiking trails. The park features stunning 500-foot quartzite bluffs, picnic areas, swimming beaches, paddling, and year-round naturalist programs. It offers accessible amenities including wheelchair-accessible entrances, parking, and trails.
title: Devil's Lake State Park
